                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/75: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-24T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 24, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 24—1:49 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>618. Following from American Consul at Nanking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 23, 9 p.m. Wang informed me today that he is endeavoring through
                            Chinese and Russian diplomatic representatives in Berlin to reach some
                            basis for solution of Chinese Eastern Railway situation. He said that
                            due to tense feeling and demonstrations in Russia he has ordered all
                            Chinese diplomatic and consular representatives to leave Russia.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
